ailayman.com

Vision and Web Search using Streamlit and Completions API - README
Overview
This repository contains code for a powerful and interactive web application that integrates vision capabilities with web search. The application is built using Streamlit and leverages the OpenAI Completions API, along with other APIs, for its functionalities.

Features
Vision capabilities to analyze images.
Integration with Google Custom Search for online item searches.
Interactive Streamlit web interface.
Installation and Setup
Clone the repository to your local machine.
Navigate to the repository's root directory in your terminal.
Step 1: Setting up the Environment
Run STEP1_Setup_Wizard.py to create a virtual environment and install the required packages.
The script will prompt for API keys and other necessary details to configure the application.
Step 2: Running the Application
Execute STEP2_Run_VisionWebSearch.py to start the Streamlit application.
The web interface allows image uploads and processes them for vision analysis and online searches.
Requirements
Python 3.x
OpenAI API key
Google API key and CSE ID
Other Python packages as listed in REQUIRED_PACKAGES within STEP1_Setup_Wizard.py.
Usage
Follow on-screen instructions in the Streamlit interface to upload images and input queries.
The application will process the input and provide relevant search results.
